   &UR; INTERNATIONAL _ (Moved in ``i'' category)  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   FRANCE-VOLCANO (St.-Ours, France) _ Louis XIV built Versailles.
President Francois Mitterrand rebuilt the Louvre. Now his
predecessor, former President Valery Giscard d'Estaing, plans to
build his own monument. A volcano. By Craig R. Whitney.
</P>
<P>
   (ART ADV: Locator map has been sent to NYT graphics clients.)
</P>
<P>
   TURTLE-WOMAN (Dalyan, Turkey) _ On many nights this summer, a
mysterious and wondrous spectacle has been unfolding on the beach
of this Mediterranean town. Beginning soon after dark, dozens of
giant loggerhead turtles, some a century old or older, emerge from
the waves, lumber up the sand, dig 3-foot-deep holes and deposit
100 or more eggs before returning to the sea. Not far from the
shoreline, a British-born woman who has made Turkey her home sits
contentedly in a house made largely of driftwood. Without her, the
sea turtles might have lost their breeding ground here, one of the
most important in this part of the world. By Stephen Kinzer.
</P>
<P>
   (ART ADV: Locator map has been sent to NYT graphics clients.)
</P>
