<P>
   MOVIE-REVIEW-PARENT _ If you didn't know that this new Parent
Trap comes courtesy of the same team behind the 1991 remake of
Father of the Bride (and its sequel), here's a clue. Just look at
the houses. So, what's the big deal, you may ask, especially when
there's a good story to be told? Details don't intrude. They just
add, well, detail. But in the Meyers/Shyer formula, details become
the means to an end. They overwhelm the story, the acting, the
pacing. (Passy, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
