   MOVIEREVIEW-NEGOTIATOR _ The Negotiator features a duel of great
minds. Too bad they don't belong to the filmmakers. Once again, a
Hollywood movie allows its premise to go poof, wasting two good
actors who register average performances. Samuel L. Jackson and
Kevin Spacey play hostage negotiators facing each other in a
psychological tango that could turn deadly. (Schwan, Palm Beach
Post) MOVED.
</P>
