<P>
   STATESCHOOL-BUS _ AUSTIN _ Throughout this fireball summer,
nearly 40 people with mental retardation were forced to endure bus
rides on the Austin State School campus in an unair-conditioned bus
where temperatures soared to 110 degrees. State inspectors deemed
the situation life-threatening, particularly because some of the
disabled residents have seizure disorders and take anticonvulsant
drugs that put them at high risk for heat stroke. (Gamino, Austin
American-Statesman) MOVED.
