<P>
   GARFIELD _ Garfield, the fat cat created by artist Jim Davis, is
celebrating his 20th birthday, prompting the International Museum
of Cartoon Art in Boca Raton, Fla., to stage an exhibition
featuring the feisty feline through Oct. 31.
</P>
<P>
   It's as good an excuse as any this summer to check out Boca, the
booming Palm Beach County resort that is steadily gaining a
reputation for brainy as well as beachy attractions. (Patureau,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED 7/28.
</P>
<P>
   AUSTIN-HOSTEL _ AUSTIN _ If hostels are, as one veteran traveler
said, the windows through which a city is viewed, then the Austin
hostel is a one-way mirror. The modest building on Lakeshore Drive
is tucked away on the southeast side of Town Lake, unseen by most
of the city's bustling downtown and university populations. Our
hostel is so nondescript even neighbors stop to ask what it is
(''It's what?'' they reply. ``A hotel? A hospital?''). Looks can be
deceiving. Inside this small hostel, more than 9,000 visitors from
every corner of the globe each year make a temporary home in 40
beds. (Hibberd, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   LOW-AIRFARE _ DELRAY BEACH, Fla. _ The Travel Company of Delray
Beach is installing computer software that quickly searches all
airfares available to find the lowest rate, the company announced
at its first annual meeting recently. The system, called Flight
Attendant, ``does what a perfect travel agent would do: searches,
searches, searches'' until it finds plane tickets that fit the
customer's needs, Chairman Joseph Vittoria said. The installation
of the system, which will occur at its subsidiary Travel 800, is
central to The Travel Company's intention of offering one-stop
shopping for travel. (Plunkett, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
