<P>
   OSTEOPOROSIS _ The alternative to estrogen to treat osteoporosis
now has been tested in people who've lost bone mass because they
took steroids for asthma or arthritis. The result: it works well.
(Lee, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   TEXAS-PARASITES _ AUSTIN _ As an outbreak of a parasitic
infection worsened _ five more people tested positive _Austin Mayor
Kirk Watson promised help to those affected by the sewage spill in
the Brushy Creek area and began demanding answers about how well
the city responded. The additional positive tests means that nine
of 12 people who submitted samples to health officials were found
to be infected with Cryptosporidium, a relatively rare and highly
infectious parasite that apparently has spread to drinking water in
the Brushy Creek area west of Round Rock. State and local health
officials said the number of positive tests qualified as an
``outbreak.'' (Davenport, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   SALAMANDER-CONSERVATION _ AUSTIN _ Swimmer after swimmer at an
Austin, Texas public hearing recently criticized a proposed
salamander-conservation plan that calls for a new dam, reduced
cleanings and other changes intended to accommodate the endangered
amphibians while allowing public use of Barton Springs Pool. Jack
Lawrence, a computer programmer and 25-year pool user, said
swimmers are ``the truly endangered species.'' (Haurwitz, Austin
American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
