<P>
   &QL;  CONGRESSMEN WILL RAISE HAMMERS TO BUILD AFFORDABLE HOUSING
</P>
<P>
   By Mark D. Preston
</P>
<P>
   States News Service
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON, June 4 -- Rarely do Democrats and Republicans agree
how to solve homelessness, but this weekend House members will
return to their districts cast partisan differences aside and
attack the problem head on.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-07-29-98 1311EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
