<SLUG> BC-WOM-SPORTS-COLUMN-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
WHO SAYS YOU CAN'T GO HOME AGAIN? 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By BARBARA HUEBNER  
 c.1998 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; After a triumphant but exhausting victory at the Goodwill
Games in her final heptathlon last week,  &UR; Jackie Joyner-Kersee
 &LR; went home to Illinois for a farewell meet in her honor Saturday
where spectators cheered her every move even though she could
muster a jump no farther than 20 feet, 11 3/4 inches _ almost 4
feet shy of her all-time best.
</P>
<P>
   ``It wasn't meant to be,'' she said afterward in her last
competition before retirement.
</P>
<P>
   But her sixth-place finish seemed to faze neither Joyner-Jersee
nor the 9,200 admirers who came out to the US Open meet at
Edwardsville, Ill., to say goodbye. Ralph Korte Stadium is about 20
miles from East St. Louis, where the 36-year-old four-time Olympian
was raised.
</P>
<P>
   Emotional tributes came from many quarters.  &UR; Gordon Bush &LR; , the
mayor of East St. Louis, proclaimed Saturday Jackie Joyner-Kersee
Day. USA Track &AMP; Field retired a uniform in her name, with its No.
7 representing the number of events in the heptathlon. The family
of retired track star Carl Lewis presented her with a check for
$5,000 for her foundation, which serves children in her rundown
hometown. The track team from her old high school ran a lap of
honor with her as she carried a lighted Olympic torch.
</P>
<P>
   Nonetheless, the woman many call the greatest female athlete of
her generation appeared to have no qualms about never competing
again.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm glad,'' she said. ``I have no regrets.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 

Fast forward
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The Boston Renegades will host the W-League's first-division
championships on Aug. 14 and 16 at Bowditch Field in Framingham.
With its 10-2 record, the Renegades get an automatic berth to the
Final Four-style tournament, with semifinal matches on Friday night
and the third-place game and final on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   ``It is only natural that Boston play host,'' said  &UR; Francisco
Marcos &LR; , &UR;  &LR; commissioner of the United Systems of Independent Soccer
Leagues. ``We are delighted to be in the Boston area, which has
been very supportive to women's soccer.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The day before the start of the Goodwill Games figure skating
competition,  &UR; Michelle Kwan  &LR; watched a tape of her silver medal
performance in the Olympics. ``I thought it was good,'' she said,
but ``I saw things I can improve on. There are some things I could
have done better. I needed a little more oomph to the long
program.'' Now, Kwan hopes the oomph is there and she can maintain
it right through the next four years to the 2002 Olympics in Salt
Lake City. She is positive about the prospects.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   By virtue of its 1-0, extra-inning victory Tuesday over host
Japan in the ISF Women's World Championship, the US national
softball team earned the right to defend its Olympic title in
Sydney. The US didn't get a hit against the tough Japanese squad
until the top of the sixth, and couldn't score until  &UR; Sheila
Douty &LR; , &UR;  &LR; of Diamond Bar, Calif., sent the first pitch of the ninth
towering over the left-field fence to give the US the lead and
eventually the win.  &UR; Lisa Fernandez  &LR; struck out 11 while allowing
just four hits and a walk in the shutout. The US faces Australia
tomorrow as the tournament continues ...  &UR; Valerie Still &LR; , &UR;  &LR; two-time
MVP of the ABL championship series, has signed a two-year contract
extension. The 37-year-old Still is the second-oldest player in the
league, but has led the Columbus Quest to two straight
championships, last season averaging 13.1 points, 7.2 rebounds, and
2.3 steals per game. At the same time she revealed that reports of
her imminent retirement were greatly exaggerated, Still announced
that the ABL has contributed $5,000 to her SKIP _ Still Kids
Improvement Program _ Foundation.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Wire service material was used to prepare this report.)
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
