of additional survivors from a series of tidal waves that crashed
into the northwestern coast of the island of New Guinea last week
and killed an estimated 3,000 people. The search for bodies
continues as Secretary of State Albright arrives here to announce
U.S. aid to help pay for the rescue effort and to install a seismic
early-warning system to prevent similar loss of life from tsunamis
in the future. By Philip Shenon.
