<P>
   RACING-BRICKYARD _ For more than 40 years, Indianapolis Motor
Speedway was the kingdom of Indy-car racing, dominated by the Foyts
and Penskes. But when NASCAR took its circuit there for the first
time in 1994, nobody could envision what would take place: that
NASCAR would turn the Brickyard into a ``Good Ol Boy'' track.
(McCollister, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   RACING-IRL _ With the IRL coming to Atlanta Motor Speedway in
August, drivers test at the Hampton facility Tuesday and Wednesday
nights. Reporting on the speeds and sights and sounds of the
Indy-cars on the Atlanta oval. (Mitchell, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   RACING-NOTEBOOK _ Motorsports notebook. (Mitchell, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   ARCHDEACON-GORDON _Jeff Gordon at age 26 he is stock car's
poster child for the next generation. He just won Sunday at Pocono
_ his fifth win this season _ and leads the point standings again.
He's already won two driving championships, 34 races and last year
made $6.5 million just in endorsements for everything from
toothpaste to milk. (Archdeacon, Dayton Daily News) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   TYSON _ TRENTON N.J. _ Mike Tyson applies today for
reinstatement as a heavyweight boxer to fight in New Jersey. A year
under suspension because he bit Evander Holyfield's ear. Tyson
returns yet again at a time when heavyweight boxing is flailing.
Holyfield can't draw fans at the Garden, Akinwande has the
hepatitis B virus, Holyfield and Lennox Lewis can't get together .
. . (Schultz, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
