   RACING-BRICKYARD _ For more than 40 years, Indianapolis Motor
Speedway was the kingdom of Indy-car racing, dominated by the Foyts
and Penskes. But when NASCAR took its circuit there for the first
time in 1994, nobody could envision what would take place: that
NASCAR would turn the Brickyard into a ``Good Ol Boy'' track.
(McCollister, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
