Telling You for the Last Time,'' but a better title would be
``Don't Stop Me If You've Heard This One.'' By TIMOTHY FINN. Story
will move in ``e'' category.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIE-NEGOTIATOR- REVIEW _ (UNDATED) The makers of ``The
Negotiator'' deserve some credit for trying to stretch the fairly
narrow parameters of the action genre. Here's a film in which
palaver tries to be as important as firepower. The problem, of
course, is that director F. Gary Gray (``Set It Off'') is still
making an action movie. Every time the talk starts to get
interesting, he feels compelled to deliver a violent sequence, lest
the audience get restless. By ROBERT W. BUTLER. Story will move in
``e'' category.
</P>
<P>
   TELEVISION-UPN-KANSAS (PASADENA, Calif.) _ The No. 5 and No. 6
networks, WB and UPN, have fallen into the same pattern as their
more-established rivals. They are taking their current hits,
crafting careful approximations of them and then hoping viewers
will show up for these ``new'' programs. By AARON BARNHART. Story
will move in ``e'' category.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIE-PARENT-REVIEW _ (UNDATED) _ So is the remake of ``The
Parent Trap''_ which originally starred Hayley Mills as identical
twins who switch identities in a kooky plan to reunite their
divorced parents _ anywhere near as good as the film that became an
instant family favorite in 1961? Hold on to your autographed
8-by-10 glossies, Mills fans. The new ``Parent Trap'' may be even
better than the movie you hold dear to your childhood. By BRIAN
McTAVISH. Story will move in ``e'' category.
