constantly tinkering with what we eat, but change is a hit-and-miss
proposition, to be sure. Take fruit, for example. Breeders both
private and government-sponsored are always crossing one fruit with
another, or different strains of the same, trying to improve on
nature, or on the latest human-made hybrid. By KAREN UHLENHUTH.
Story will move in the ``l'' category.
