<P>
   CALIFORNIA -- RIGGS. (Possible.) Congress is expected to vote on
an amendment by Frank Riggs, R-Napa, that would deny federal
housing funds to San Francisco unless it repeals a law that forces
companies doing business with the city to provide domestic
partnership benefits. Zaret
</P>
<P>
   COLORADO -- BUDGET. When given the choice between tax breaks and
increased spending, 90 percent of people who participated in a
recent study said they would choose door number three -- paying
back the debt. And more than three-fourths of the participants
would include an individual savings account as part of any Social
Security reform measure. The study, by the non-profit Committee for
a Responsible Federal Budget, gave 850 people in five cities --
including Denver -- the chance to spend a day working through some
of the decisions legislators face in creating the federal budget.
Zaret
</P>
<P>
   CONNECTICUT -- HMO. Saying neither the Democratic nor the
Republican health care reform bills have enough support to pass the
Senate, a coalition of senators, including Sen. Joseph I.
Lieberman, today introduced a bill they consider a ``centrist''
approach to creating a slate of patient protections. Maggi
</P>
