articles are transmitted every week.) 
 (PLEASE NOTE: This article has been transmitted into the ``i''
international and ``f'' financial files.) 
 By SERGIO R. BUSTOS 
 c.1998 Latin Trade 
 (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) 
 &HT;    
 &HT;    SAN JOSE, Costa Rica _ Everybody in Costa Rica seems to know the
road to the new location of U.S. technology giant Intel. Of course,
it's hard to miss the massive construction site of a company that
is the world's biggest computer chip maker. A company that
surprisingly chose Costa Rica to locate its latest assembly and
