<HEADLINE>
&HT;    
 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Delving into Hayley Mills: There's much more than `Parent Trap'
 &HT;    By Jill Vejnoska
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Hollywood toys with remaking ``Casablanca'' and we don't even
blink. Another ``It's a Wonderful Life''? Hey, what would be
wonderful-er?
</P>
<P>
   But remake ``The Parent Trap''? Now they've gone too far. The
classic 1961 comedy, about identical twins scheming to reunite
their divorced parents, made millions for Walt Disney's film
company and turned 15-year-old star Hayley Mills into a household
name, household name. (She played both parts.)
</P>
<P>
   While her six Disney movies were hugely popular, their success
boomeranged on Mills in a way. At 20, she did a nude scene in ``The
Family Way,'' and some fans had trouble reconciling it with her
innocent past.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Family Way'' is among our recommended Mills movies on
video:
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Tiger Bay'' (1959)
</P>
<P>
   What it's about: A hyper-imaginative girl witnesses a murder and
befriends the killer. No one believes her, and the situation
spirals out of control.
</P>
<P>
   Who's in it: John Mills, Horst Buchholz.
</P>
<P>
   Hayley, yeah! Originally the part called for a boy. But while
visiting distinguished actor John Mills, the filmmakers were taken
with his 12-year-old daughter Hayley, and a rewrite quickly
followed.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Pollyanna'' (1960)
</P>
<P>
   What it's about: An orphan moves in with her aunt, who's rich,
cold and living in a town where almost nobody gets along. But the
relentlessly cheerful little girl with the curls soon changes all
that.
</P>
<P>
   Who's in it: Jane Wyman (post-Ronald Reagan, pre-``Falcon
Crest''), Karl Malden, Agnes (``Bewitched'') Moorehead.
</P>
<P>
   Hayley , yeah! Mills' special Academy Award for an outstanding
juvenile performance was presented by _ speaking of relentlessly
cheerful girls with curls _ Shirley Temple.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Whistle Down the Wind'' (1961)
</P>
<P>
   What it's about: Three emotionally needy British children find a
mysterious man hiding in their barn and believe he's Jesus Christ.
Children come from miles around to meet him and to keep his
presence a secret from doubting adults.
</P>
<P>
   Who's in it: Alan Bates, Bernard Lee.
</P>
<P>
   Hayley, yeah! This black-and-white movie was based on a novel
written by Mary Hayley Bell, Hayley's mother. Sir Andrew Lloyd
Webber's musical version recently opened in London.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``The Chalk Garden'' (1964)
</P>
<P>
   What it's about: A troubled teenager living in her grandmother's
seaside mansion spends her days setting fires and getting five
governesses fired. When a mysterious No. 6 arrives, a fierce battle
of wills ensues.
</P>
<P>
   Who's in it: Deborah Kerr, John Mills, Edith Evans.
</P>
<P>
   Hayley, yeah! Earlier, Kerr had won an Oscar nomination for
``The King and I.'' Last year, Hayley Mills toured American
theaters in the same role Kerr played.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``The Trouble With Angels'' (1966)
</P>
<P>
   What it's about: Comic misadventures of a group of fun-loving
girls at a convent boarding school. They don't really want to be
there, so there's no chance that any of them will decide to become
nuns _ is there?
</P>
<P>
   Who's in it: Rosalind Russell, Gypsy Rose Lee (!), Jim Hutton,
June Harding.
</P>
<P>
   Hayley, yeah! This spawned a sequel, ``Where Angels Go ...
Trouble Follows'' (1968). Mills wasn't in it, maybe because she
didn't want to co-star with Stella Stevens, Arthur Godfrey and
Milton Berle.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``The Family Way'' (1966)
</P>
<P>
   What it's about: Young newlyweds' problems, from impotence
(before Viagra) to _ worse _ moving in with the in-laws.
</P>
<P>
   Who's in it: Hywel Bennett, John Mills (him again!), Marjorie
Rhodes, Murray Head.
</P>
<P>
   Who did the music: The score was written by the ``cute'' Beatle
himself, Paul McCartney.
</P>
<P>
   Hayley, yeah! Mills ended up marrying the film's 53-year-old
director, Roy Boulting, in 1971.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Endless Night'' (1971)
</P>
<P>
   What it's about: A chauffeur marries a rich American girl, and
they move into their dream house. It's based on an Agatha Christie
mystery, so guess how the dream turns out.
</P>
<P>
   Who's in it: George Sanders, Hywel Bennett, Britt Ekland, Peter
Bowles.
</P>
<P>
   Hayley, yeah! In the movie, once again she's married to her
``Family Way'' spouse, Bennett. Don't these two ever learn?
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
