<P>
   Here are the business news stories the Los Angeles Daily News
plans to move for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs
of Thursday, July 30 and thereafter. The stories will carry the
``f'' financial news category code unless otherwise noted. For
questions about stories, contact Stewart Slavin at the Daily News,
(818) 713-3702.
</P>
<P>
   ACT-LAYOFFS (Camarillo, Calif.) _ ACT Networks will lay off
one-fourth of its employees after the company reported poor
fourth-quarter and year-end results. By Dave McNary.
</P>
<P>
   WESTFIELD-EARNINGS (Los Angeles) _ Westfield America Inc.
announced strong quarterly earnings Wednesday, reflecting the
strong retail climate in California and the other states it owns
shopping centers. By Enrique Rivero.
</P>
