<HEADLINE>
SOME TRAVEL DISCOUNTS  
 (FOR RELEASE SUNDAY, AUG. 2) 
</HEADLINE>
   (af)  
 By JANET PIORKO   
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   CRUISING IN ASIA Holland America is offering 50 percent
discounts on three 15-day cruises of the 1,214-passenger Nieuw
Amsterdam between Hong Kong and Singapore this fall.
</P>
<P>
   With the discounts, fares start at $2,113 a person, double
occupancy; round-trip air from the East Coast is an additional
$999. The discounts apply to the Oct. 20 and Nov. 19 sailings from
Hong Kong to Singapore and the Nov. 4 sailing in reverse.
</P>
<P>
   Among the ports are Da Nang, Vietnam; Siracha, Thailand; Muara,
Brunei; Kota Kinabalu, Malaysia; Port Kelang, Malaysia. On the Hong
Kong-Singapore itinerary, the ship spends two days in Hong Kong; on
the reverse itinerary, it spends two days in Thailand. Reservations
must be made through travel agents; for more information, the line
has a Web site: www.holland-america.com. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   BAJA BARGAIN The Hotel Twin Dolphin, six miles northeast of Cabo
San Lucas on the Baja Peninsula, has summer rates of $175 a night
until Oct. 31; guests also receive a credit of $30 a room daily
toward food and beverages.
</P>
<P>
   In addition, those who stay three nights before Sept. 30 can
spend a fourth night at no extra charge. The 50-room oceanfront
hotel is situated on 135 acres; there are no telephones,
televisions, clocks or radios in guest rooms. All rooms have ocean
views. Reservations: (800) 421-8925. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   GALAPAGOS BOUND General Tours is offering a new six-night
combination cruise and tour to the Galapagos starting at $1,999 a
person including air fare from Miami. The lowest price is for
August through October departures; in November and December the
price is $2,399, and in January through March of next year, $2,549.
(Air fare from New York is an extra $175 round trip.)
</P>
<P>
   The itinerary includes a four-night cruise through the islands
on board the new 100-passenger, all-suite Galapagos Explorer II.
The program also features two nights in Quito, buffet breakfast
daily and all meals during the cruise. Reservations: (800)
221-2216. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   THAILAND FOR LESS Saga Holidays has dropped the price by $400,
to $1,999 a person, double occupancy, on three departures of an
18-night Discovering Thailand trip to Bangkok and Chiang Mai. The
departures are Sept. 29, Oct. 13 and Oct. 27. (In late July the
Oct. 13 tour was almost full.) September is very rainy, averaging
12 inches in Bangkok, 10 in Chiang Mai; October averages 8 and 4
inches respectively.
</P>
<P>
   There are also trips next year starting at $2,199. The price
includes accommodations with daily buffet breakfast, most dinners,
some excursions and air fare from the eastern United States.
</P>
<P>
   The company's packages are designed for travelers 50 and older.
Lodging in Chiang Mai is at the 370-room Imperial Mae Ping Hotel,
which has a small outdoor swimming pool. Guest rooms are
air-conditioned and have private baths with showers. Reservations:
(800) 343-0273.
</P>
</TEXT>
