HISPANIC-LEADERS (Phoenix) - Phoenix is the 6th largest city in the
country with a sizable Hispanic population. Yet there are no
hispanics in the city manager's office with the departure of David
Garcia. there also isn't a Hispanic City Council member. Only one
department head is Hispanic. National and local Hispanic leaders
are putting the pressure on Phoenix City Hall, meeting with city
leaders Thursday to discuss the shortage of Hispanics in key city
positions. By CHRIS FISCUS and RUBEN NAVARRETTE JR. Story will move
in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
ASTEROID (Flagstaff, Ariz.) - A mile-wide asteroid that could one
day collide with our Earth, and destroy life on our planet, was
discovered recently by Arizona scientists using a new device
specifically designed to search for potential killer space rocks.
Dubbed ``1998 MQ,'' the asteroid is the first near-Earth space
debris discovered by Lowell Observatory's Near-Earth Object Search,
or LONEOS, which began scanning the night skies from Flagstaff in
March. LONEOS is part of a larger project funded by NASA, which has
the goal of discovering at least 90 percent of all near-Earth
objects within the next decade, thereby providing an early warning
system for any objects in space that could pose a threat to human
survival. With GRAPHIC. By STEVE YOZWIAK. Story moved in the ``A``
category. &QL; 
