<TEXT>
<P>
   The following Arizona Republic stories have been added for use
by clients of the NYTimes News Service for Thursday, July 30. If
you have any questions, please contact the Republic News Desk at
(602) 271-8286.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
TRW (Mesa, Ariz.) - TRW is slashing 14 percent of its workforce and
closing as many as 21 automotive factories. The 7,500 workers for
the Cleveland-based company won't know till later this year or even
next if they have jobs, but a TRW spokesman said the company will
target its least-profitable operations. That likely won't mean its
airbag operations, which are No. 1 in volume in the United States.
Story will include worker reax. By
</P>
<P>
   KERRY FEHR-SNYDER and CRAIG ANDERSON. Story will move in the
``F'' category.  &QL; 
 &QL; 
CHIPS (Phoenix) - Mi Ranchito says its snack chips are getting
pushed out of grocery aisles due to an aggressive campaign by
Frito-Lay to buy up as much shelf space as it can. The company
already is out of most grocery chains and says it could be out of
business if it loses more space. By GLEN CRENO. Story will move in
the ``F'' category. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
