<P>
   (NYT10) NEW YORK -- July 29, 1998 -- DE-LA-GUARDA-THEATER, 7-29
-- Everybody gets into the act in De la Guarda's ``Villa Villa'' at
the Daryl Roth Theater. The show has no seats, no plot, no dialogue
and a predominantly young, casual clientele. But along the way it
is becoming one of the most talked about and puzzled over Off
Broadway productions of the year, one that has raised in a
particularly fevered way one of the theater's enduring obsessions:
how to get a generation raised on MTV interested in seeing live
theater. (Nancy Siesel/New York Times Photo)
