7-29 -- Theodore Luttwak sells imported Italian marble to wealthy
Nigerians at what he advertises are ``very, very, very, very
competitive prices.'' Abuja, Nigeria's capital-under-construction,
is full of the whiff of oil money and Luttwak - ``just call me
Teddy'' - is out to get his share of the $10 billion that Nigeria
earns each year from oil. ``Look, the human rights here in Nigeria
are terrible, but the opportunities are just fantastic,'' he says.
``Tell me, where else in the world do you have so much money?''
(Roger Cohen/New York Times Photo)
