(Philip Greenberg/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT13) UNDATED -- July 29, 1998 -- CIR-COMPUTER-SPEAKERS, 7-29
-- At right is the Powercube Plus Multimedia Speaker System. It
includes two plastic molded satellites, each 3- by 5- inches, with
both a 3-inch full-range driver, and a 3/4-inch tweeter and a
6-inch woofer in a compact, 14-by-12-by-8-inch wooden cabinet. At
left, Bose Mediamate system. It offers fine midbass performance
from one tiny 2.5-inch full-range speaker in each wedge-shaped,
front-ported, plastic cabinet. (Naum Kazhdan/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT12) NEW YORK -- July 29, 1998 -- OBIT-ROBBINS-2-B&AMP;W, 7-29 --
Jerome Robbins supervises a rehearsal of the New York City Ballet
earlier this year. Robbins, who simultaneously became one of
20th-century ballet's greatest choreographers and a towering
innovator in Broadway musicals, died Wednesday at his home in
Manhattan at the age of 79. His golden touch was evident in
musicals as disparate as ``On the Town,'' ``The King and I,''
``Gypsy,'' ``West Side Story'' and ``Fiddler on the Roof.'' (Paul
Kolnik/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT11) NEW YORK -- July 29, 1998 -- OBIT-ROBBINS-1-B&AMP;W, 7-29 --
Jerome Robbins supervises a rehearsal of the New York City Ballet
earlier this year. Robbins, who simultaneously became one of
20th-century ballet's greatest choreographers and a towering
innovator in Broadway musicals, died Wednesday at his home in
Manhattan at the age of 79. His golden touch was evident in
musicals as disparate as ``On the Town,'' ``The King and I,''
``Gypsy,'' ``West Side Story'' and ``Fiddler on the Roof.'' (Paul
Kolnik/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT10) NEW YORK -- July 29, 1998 -- DE-LA-GUARDA-THEATER, 7-29
-- Everybody gets into the act in De la Guarda's ``Villa Villa'' at
the Daryl Roth Theater. The show has no seats, no plot, no dialogue
and a predominantly young, casual clientele. But along the way it
is becoming one of the most talked about and puzzled over Off
Broadway productions of the year, one that has raised in a
particularly fevered way one of the theater's enduring obsessions:
how to get a generation raised on MTV interested in seeing live
theater. (Nancy Siesel/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT9) UNDATED -- July 29, 1998 -- CIR-NET-POLITICS-2, 7-29 --
One of the most watched Web sites in politics is for the campaign
of Jeb Bush, the likely Republican candidate for governor of
Florida. Known as the ``Jeb site,'' it is the envy of Internet
political consultants, a $26,000 site in a field where $5,000 is
the going rate. (New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT8) UNDATED -- July 29, 1998 -- CIR-NET-POLITICS-1, 7-29 --
Sen. Barbara Boxer, D-Calif., uses her website to keep her
constituents informed. Visitors to her site can sign up others to
receive message about the senator via e-mail. The feature has been
used 50 or 60 times at the site in recent months. (New York Times
Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT7) WACONIA, Minn. -- July 29, 1998 -- CIR-SHOPPING-ONLINE,
