<HEADLINE>
FAMOUS LAST WORDS FROM THE PRESS TOUR 
</HEADLINE>
   By JOHN CARMAN  
 c.1998, San Francisco Chronicle  
<TEXT>
<P>
   PASADENA, Calif. _ They said it on the TV press tour:
</P>
<P>
   _ &LR;   &LR; ``Well, they were listening, and they weren't yelling lewd
things to us in the middle of a scene'' _ Christina Applegate,
comparing the studio audience at her new series, ``Jesse,'' with
the ``Married ... With Children'' studio audience.
</P>
<P>
   _ &LR;   &LR; ``We sort of made the deal contingent on nothing except my
incredible talent. Then we panicked'' _ actor Brian Benben of ``The
Brian Benben Show.''
</P>
<P>
   _ &LR;   &LR; ``You guys have to be easy on me. I'm a virgin up here. I'm
like having a heart attack up here'' _ Joanne Waters, creator and
producer of ``To Have and to Hold.''
</P>
<P>
   _ &LR;   &LR; ``I liked it. I was hungry, though. I snacked through the
whole thing'' _ Waters, on reading ``Angela's Ashes.''
</P>
<P>
   _ &LR;   &LR; ``People ask me, `What kind of belt do you have?' Well, my
belt is Gucci belt'' _ director and martial arts stuntman Stanley
Tong.
</P>
<P>
   _ &LR;   &LR; ``You don't. You're in there rooting for somebody to go
down. What do you think, we're crazy?'' _ William Devane, asked
about resisting the temptation to hope another show fails so his
show (``Turks'') can get a time slot.
</P>
<P>
   _ &LR;   &LR; ``I trashed them right from the start. All the people I
hated, I got even'' _ former quarterback Phil Simms, asked if it
was hard to turn broadcaster and criticize players.
</P>
<P>
   _ &LR;   &LR; ``This is my nightmare, and you know why? Because I went to
the set beforehand, and they did my hair and my makeup, and I look
like a French prostitute'' _ Waters.
</P>
<P>
   _ &LR;   &LR; ``I pursued a career. It eluded me'' _ Kari Lizer, on giving
up acting to become an executive producer.
</P>
<P>
   _ &LR;   &LR; ``It's really who hates us less at any given moment'' _
producer Marcy Carsey, on knowing which network to approach to
pitch a new series.
</P>
<P>
   _ &LR;   &LR; ``In like the theater, they want to like hop in the abyss
and stay in there for 15 minutes, you know, and suffer for their
art. I never had any plans of being a starving artist. I came out
to Los Angeles to write for film and television because I wanted to
make a lot of cash'' _ Waters.
</P>
<P>
   _ &LR;   &LR; ``We had Jay Leno on `The Simpsons' once. Do you know how
impossible it is to draw Jay Leno, with that chin, for that show?''
_ ``Simpsons'' creator Matt Groening.
</P>
<P>
   _ &LR;   &LR; ``Takes smart people to write them. Too many people are
spending too much time watching television'' _ producer Diane
English, asked why there are no more ``smart'' shows.
</P>
<P>
   _ &LR;   &LR; ``I was living in a room in Hollywood. So I would have
written a show about homosexual parakeets, you understand what I
mean?'' _ Waters, on writing a failed series pilot.
</P>
<P>
   _ &LR;   &LR; ``Joanne, in your show about homosexual parakeets, would you
have shown the characters kissing?'' _ critic's question to Waters.
</P>
<P>
   _ &LR;   &LR; ``They sent a box to the hotel room we were in. I mean, we
had a weekend basically to really get into `The Brady Bunch.' And
we watched about 25 hours of `Brady Bunch' episodes. It is Fellini
if you watch 25 hours of `Brady Bunch' episodes back to back. You
start to realize Jan has voices in her head'' _ Bonnie Turner, who
wrote ``The Brady Bunch Movie'' with her husband, Terry.
</P>
<P>
   _ &LR;   &LR; ``Any time I don't have to look at the Nielsen ratings, I
consider it a joyous time in my life'' _ Tom Fontana, executive
producer of ``Homicide: Life on the Street.''
</P>
<P>
   _ &LR;   &LR; ``There are some differences. You know, like the pants can
only come halfway off. But I find that for me, that's enough'' _
Brian Benben, comparing network TV with pay cable.
</P>
<P>
   _ &LR;   &LR; ``There's nothing more fun than waking up at 6 o'clock on a
Sunday morning, putting on a suit and tie, and coming to see you
guys'' _ Valentine.
</P>
<P>
   _ &LR;   &LR; ``Likewise'' _ Tom Jicha, TV critic, Fort Lauderdale
Sun-Sentinel.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
