<DOCNO> NYT19980729.0549 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-29 22:00 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A9415 &Cx1f; taf-z
u k &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-EDIT-CLINTON-STARR-1S     07-29 0615
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-EDIT-CLINTON-STARR-1STLD-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
EDITORIAL: AN APPOINTMENT WITH TRUTH? 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (EDS: Subs to correct publication date to Thursday, July 30.)  (th) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   The New York Times said in an editorial on Thursday, July 30:
</P>
<P>
   President Clinton and independent counsel Kenneth Starr have
reached a reasonable compromise in the deal to have Clinton testify
at the White House rather than before a grand jury. That is a
